#### GUI-008: Implement "Self-Healing" on Syntax Error
**Points: 2 | Priority: Medium**

**Description:** Implement error recovery system that maintains Mirror-Canvas sync even when code has syntax errors.

**Technical Requirements:**
- Parse partial/invalid TypeScript code gracefully
- Maintain last valid AST state during syntax errors
- Display meaningful error diagnostics in Monaco editor
- Prevent sync crashes when compilation fails
- Provide AI-assisted error correction suggestions

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Syntax errors in code pane don't break visual timeline
- [ ] Error diagnostics show precise location and description
- [ ] Last valid experiment state preserved during error recovery
- [ ] Visual timeline highlights problematic components
- [ ] AI assistant suggests fixes for common syntax errors
- [ ] Real-time error feedback as user types

**Implementation Details:**
```typescript
// @psyforge/error-recovery
export class SyntaxErrorRecovery {
  private lastValidAST: ExperimentAST | null = null;
  private errorState: SyntaxError | null = null;

  async attemptCompilation(code: string): Promise<CompilationResult> {
    try {
      const ast = await this.compiler.compile(code);
      this.lastValidAST = ast;
      this.errorState = null;
      return { success: true, ast };
    } catch (error) {
      this.errorState = error;
      return { 
        success: false, 
        error, 
        lastValidAST: this.lastValidAST,
        suggestions: await this.generateFixSuggestions(code, error)
      };
    }
  }

  private async generateFixSuggestions(code: string, error: SyntaxError): Promise<FixSuggestion[]> {
    // AI-assisted error correction
    return this.aiAssistant.suggestFixes(code, error);
  }
}
```

